{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Security Leak Scan",
  "description": "Scans generated code for security issues and lists findings by severity. Does NOT auto-fix — use the companion 'Apply Security Fixes' hook to apply fixes.",
  "version": "2",
  "when": {
    "type": "agentStop"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "IMPORTANT: Skip this analysis entirely if the only edited files are under `.kiro/specs/`, `docs/`, or are documentation markdown files (README.md, AGENT.md, CLAUDE.md, QUICK_START.md, GITHUB_SUBMISSION.md). Only analyze actual source code changes.\n\nReview changed files for potential security issues.\n\n**List all findings with severity (DO NOT auto-fix anything):**\nScan for these issues and list each with a severity (🔴 Critical, 🟡 Warning, 🟢 Info):\n- Hardcoded API keys, tokens, or credentials in source code\n- Private keys or sensitive credentials\n- Encryption keys or certificates\n- Authentication tokens or session IDs\n- Passwords or secrets in configuration files\n- IP addresses containing sensitive data\n- Hardcoded internal URLs\n- Database connection credentials\n- Insecure defaults or missing input validation\n\nPresent the full list.\n\n⚠️ DO NOT edit any files. Only report findings. The developer can use the 'Apply Security Fixes' hook to fix critical items."
  }
}